{
  "id": "019d24a3-babb-7140-98dd-3b83addb2508",
  "content": "## Hooks Rust Migration — v0.4.5 (2026-03-25)\n\nAll Claude Code hooks migrated from 8 bash scripts to a single Rust entry point: `corvia hooks run --event <type> [--handler <name>]`.\n\n### Modules (crates/corvia-cli/src/hooks/)\n- mod.rs — HookEvent enum dispatch, stdin parsing\n- session.rs — JSONL WAL writer, atomic O_APPEND, stale sweep, gzip finalize\n- doc_placement.rs — Validates file paths against corvia.toml rules at Write/Edit time\n- agent_check.rs — Agent identity registration\n- reminders.rs — corvia-first and write reminders\n- cleanup.rs — WSL orphan process cleanup (throttled to 10min)\n- settings.rs — settings.json generation with hook matchers\n- status.rs — Hook status checks\n\n### Performance\n- Cold start: ~5ms (vs ~50ms for bash)\n- Atomic JSONL writes: O_APPEND with PIPE_BUF (4096) limit\n- Turn tracking: scans last 8KB of file for highest turn number\n\n### Hook Events\nSessionStart, UserPromptSubmit, PreToolUse, PostToolUse, SessionEnd\n\n### CLI Subcommands\n- corvia hooks run — execute hook (called by Claude Code)\n- corvia hooks init — generate .claude/settings.json\n- corvia hooks status — show enabled hooks\n- corvia hooks sweep — gzip stale session files",
  "source_version": "mcp",
